Preheat your grill to high. Cut the @aubergine{1} into 1cm thick slices. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into ½cm pieces. Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1} and chop into ½cm chunks. Halve, then remove the core from the @yellow pepper{1} and chop into 1cm pieces. Peel and grate all but one @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @oregano{1/2} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the @?stalks{}).

Put the aubergine slices on a #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle over some @oil{}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{}. Grill for ~{8-9%minutes} on each side, until browned and soft.

> Keep an eye on them to make sure they don't burn. If they aren't soft after this time, just leave them under your grill for a little longer.

Remove and set aside.

Meanwhile, make the tomato sauce. Put a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion. Cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the courgette and pepper with a pinch of salt and some black pepper. Cook until soft and slightly browned, ~{5%minutes}. Add the grated garlic, oregano, @tomato puree{20%g} and @cinnamon stick{1}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Next, add the @red lentils{50%g}, @Worcester sauce{1}, @vegetable stock pot{1/2} and @chopped tomatoes{1/2}. Refill the tin(s) a third with @water{} and pour that in too. Add a pinch of @sugar{pinch}. Simmer until the lentils are soft, ~{15-20%minutes}. If the sauce gets too dry, just add a splash of water.

Cut the @ciabatta{1} into 1cm thick slices and place them on another baking tray. Pop them under your grill for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side, then remove. Cut the remaining @garlic clove{1} in half and rub across both sides of the ciabatta slices. We call this 'cheat's garlic bread'!

When the tomato sauce is ready, remove the cinnamon stick and transfer the sauce to an #ovenproof dish{}. Layer over the aubergine slices. Spoon on the @creme fraiche{1} and spread it out across the top. Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and add a grind of black pepper. Put the moussaka under your grill for ~{5%minutes}, or until the cheese is golden and bubbling. Serve in bowls with the cheat's garlic bread on the side. Enjoy!